## CalibrationResult.(constructor)

Creates an instance of [CalibrationError](./assistive-playwright-client.calibrationerror.md)<!-- -->, containing the coordinates of the viewport inside the browser window. An object of this class is returned by [playwrightCalibrate()](./assistive-playwright-client.playwrightcalibrate.md) if the calibration succeeds.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
constructor(
    x: number, 
    y: number, 
    screenWidth: number, 
    screenHeight: number, 
    vm: VM, 
    frame: Page | Frame);
```
